record.text: You point to one single report looking at a very small number of studies, almost all of which involve well known flawed methods (self-reporting, correlations, small sample sizes). Your report is from 2018. Since then we have seen dozens of more comprehensive studies that have shown no evidence.

Not a single study has found a causal link between social media and harm. What correlation has been found shows the link most likely in the other direction: kids dealing with mental health challenges where the system has failed those kids, such that they turn to social media instead.
